Class AbstractSequence<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • sequences.AbstractSequence<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements that can be held in this sequence.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Deque, Queue, Stack

    public abstract class AbstractSequence<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Specifies methods that the Stack, Queue, and Deque classes must implement.
    Author:
    David Matuszek
